2engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-reports-rise-in-production-of-aluminium-iron-ore-zinc-in-q1-124070301009_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-reports-rise-in-production-of-aluminium-iron-ore-zinc-in-q1-124070301009_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fvedanta-reports-rise-in-production-of-aluminium-iron-ore-zinc-in-q1-124070301009_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2233%2C000%20Died%20Every%20Year%20In%2010%20Indian%20Cities%20Due%20To%20Rising%20Pollution%3A%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENearly%2033%2C000%20deaths%20in%2010%20cities%20in%20India%20every%20year%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20air%20pollution%20levels%20that%20are%20below%20India's%20national%20clean%20air%20threshold.%20The%20report%20has%20been%20published%20in%20the%20Lancet%20Planetary%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20clean%20air%20norms%20are%20presently%20well%20above%20the%20World%20Health%20Organisation%20guideline%20of%2015%20micrograms%20in%20every%20cubic%20meter%20of%20air.%20The%20report%20makes%20the%20point%20that%20India%20must%20drastically%20reduce%20its%20clean%20air%20norms%20to%20at%20least%20match%20WHO%20guidelines%20to%20protect%20citizens%20from%20the%20dangers%20of%20polluted%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20used%20data%20on%20PM2.5%20exposure%20in%20the%2010%20cities%20and%20the%20daily%20counts%20of%20mortality%20between%202008%20and%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20levels%20of%20air%20pollution%20below%20current%20Indian%20air%20quality%20standards%20lead%20to%20increased%20daily%20mortality%20rates%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAcross%2010%20cities%20in%20the%20country%20-%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20Chennai%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20Pune%2C%20Shimla%2C%20and%20Varanasi%2C%20around%2033%2C000%20deaths%20per%20year%20can%20be%20attributed%20to%20air%20pollution%20levels%20that%20are%20above%20the%20WHO%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20significant%20number%20of%20deaths%20were%20observed%20even%20in%20cities%20not%20considered%20to%20have%20high%20air%20pollution%2C%20such%20as%20Mumbai%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20Kolkata%2C%20and%20Chennai%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20national%20air%20quality%20standards%20should%20be%20made%20more%20stringent%2C%20and%20efforts%20to%20control%20air%20pollution%20redoubled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202008%20and%202019%2C%207.2%25%20of%20all%20deaths%20(approximately%2033%2C000%20each%20year)%20across%20all%2010%20of%20these%20cities%20could%20be%20linked%20to%20short-term%20PM2.5%20exposure%20that%20was%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20value%20of%2015%20micrograms%20in%20every%20cubic%20meter%20of%20air%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%2010%20micrograms%20in%20every%20cubic%20meter%20of%20air%20increase%20in%20short-term%20PM2.5%20exposure%20was%20associated%20with%20a%201.42%25%20increase%20in%20daily%20deaths.%20This%20estimate%20nearly%20doubled%20to%203.57%25%20when%20we%20used%20a%20causal%20modelling%20approach%20that%20isolates%20the%20impact%20of%20local%20sources%20of%20air%20pollution%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%20recorded%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20air%20pollution-related%20deaths%20in%20the%20study%20period%20-%20a%20staggering%2011.5%25%20i.e.%2012%2C000%20deaths%20each%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20deaths%20were%20attributable%20to%20short-term%20PM.5%20exposure%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%2010%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20meter%20of%20air%20increase%20in%20short-term%20PM.s%20exposure%20was%20associated%20with%20a%200.31%25%20increase%20in%20daily%20deaths.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaranasi%20logged%20the%20second%20highest%20number%20of%20deaths%20during%20the%20period%20-%2010.2%25%20or%20around%20830%20deaths%20a%20year%2C%20attributable%20to%20short-term%20PM2.5%20exposure%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20value.%20Every%2010%20micrograms%20per%20cubic%20meter%20of%20air%20increase%20in%20short-term%20PM.s%20exposure%20was%20associated%20with%20a%201.17%25%20increase%20in%20daily%20deaths%2C%20the%20study%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%202%2C100%20died%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%202%2C900%20in%20Chennai%2C%204%2C700%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20and%20around%205%2C100%20each%20year%20in%20Mumbai%20each%20year%20due%20to%20the%20rising%20air%20pollution%20during%20the%20study%20period.%20The%20deaths%20were%20all%20attributable%20to%20short-term%20PM2.5%20exposure%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lowest%20air%20pollution%20levels%20were%20recorded%20in%20Shimla.%20However%2C%20air%20pollution%20was%20still%20a%20risk%20in%20the%20hill%20city%20with%203.7%25%20of%20all%20deaths%20-%2059%20per%20year%20-%20attributable%20to%20short-term%20PM2.5%20exposure%20higher%20than%20the%20WHO%20guideline%20value.%20%26quot%3BThe%20results%20from%20Shimla%20add%20credence%20to%20global%20evidence%20that%20there%20is%20no%20safe%20level%20of%20air%20pollution%20exposure%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20highlighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20first%20multi-city%20study%20that%20assessed%20the%20relationship%20between%20short-term%20air%20pollution%20exposure%20and%20deaths%20in%20India%2C%20with%20the%20cities%20included%20spanning%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20air%20pollution%20concentrations%20and%20situated%20in%20different%20agro-climatological%20zones%2C%20a%20press%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20conducted%20by%20researchers%20from%20Sustainable%20Futures%20Collaborative%2C%20Ashoka%20University%2C