al%20successors%20to%20take%20over.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20according%20to%20campaign%20finance%20experts%2C%20she%20would%20have%20the%20easiest%20path%20to%20accessing%20the%20Biden%20campaign's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024-election%2Fbiden-campaign-money-kamala-harris-rcna159850%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24240%20million%20war%20chest%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20nobody%20is%20quite%20sure%20what%20would%20happen%20to%20the%20millions%20should%20Biden%20step%20aside%2C%20Harris%20would%20probably%20control%20the%20cash%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20if%20she%20became%20the%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Harris%20succeeded%20Biden%20as%20the%20presidential%20nominee%2C%20she%20would%20maintain%20access%20to%20all%20the%20funds%20in%20the%20campaign%20committee%20and%20could%20use%20them%20to%20advance%20her%20presidential%20candidacy%2C%26quot%3B%20Saurav%20Ghosh%2C%20the%20director%20for%20federal%20campaign%20finance%20reform%20at%20the%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20she%20shares%20a%20campaign%20committee%20with%20Biden%2C%20Ghosh%20said.%20Given%20her%20initial%20involvement%20with%20the%20Biden%20money%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20presence%20of%20her%20name%20on%20FEC%20filings%20related%20to%20his%20candidacy%20%E2%80%94%20she%20is%20likely%20the%20only%20one%20who%20could%20use%20the%20money%20without%20much%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20same%20rules%20wouldn't%20apply%20if%20Harris%20remained%20the%20vice%20presidential%20candidate%20or%20dropped%20off%20the%20ticket%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ghosh%2C%20federal%20contribution%20limits%20stipulate%20that%20candidate-to-candidate%20transfers%20don't%20exceed%20%242%2C000%20per%20election.%20While%20the%20Biden%20camp%20could%20convert%20the%20money%20into%20a%20political%20action%20committee%20if%20someone%20else%20was%20the%20nominee%2C%20there's%20a%20catch%20%E2%80%94%20PACs%20can%20only%20donate%20a%20maximum%20of%20%243%2C300%20per%20election%20to%20a%20different%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20in%20either%20case%2C%20there's%20no%20legal%20way%20for%20Biden%20to%20transfer%20to%20a%20new%20candidate%20the%20%2490%20million%20dollars%20that%20his%20campaign%20currently%20has%20on%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghosh%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20massive%20return-to-sender%20effort%2C%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20could%20also%20refund%20donations%20and%20donors%20could%20redirect%20their%20money%20toward%20the%20new%20candidate%2C%20campaign%20finance%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024-election%2Fbiden-campaign-money-kamala-harris-rcna159850%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperts%20told%20NBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Or%2C%20in%20yet%20another%20version%20of%20the%20future%2C%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20could%20transfer%20the%20funds%20to%20the%20national%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20things%20considered%2C%20Harris%20soaring%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20ticket%20if%20Biden%20steps%20aside%20seems%20like%20the%20simplest%20solution%20with%20regards%20to%20the%20cold%20hard%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20money%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20not%20the%20only%20question%20%E2%80%94%20though%20many%20heads%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-coconut-tree-memes-khive-joe-biden-debate-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturning%20in%20Harris'%3C%2Fa%3E%20direction%2C%20longstanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkamala-harris-biden-debate-newsom-whitmer-reaction-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equestions%20about%20her%20viability%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20candidate%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228a569576-be9a-4ad5-968a-00657eee2255%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHarris%20has%20major%20support%20among%20the%20Democratic%20Party's%20core.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPushing%20Harris%20aside%20could%20risk%20a%20firestorm.%20The%20vice%20president%20has%20repeatedly%20declared%20that%20she's%20standing%20behind%20Biden%2C%20but%20already%2C%20influential%20voices%20in%20the%20party%20are%20lining%20up%20behind%20her.%20Rep.%20James%20Clyburn%20of%20South%20Carolina%2C%20whose%20backing%20helped%20Biden%20win%20the%20state's%202020%20primary%2C%20has%20said%20he%20would%20want%20Harris%20if%20Biden%20drops%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20do%20everything%20we%20can%20to%20bolster%20her%2C%20whether%20it's%20in%20second%20place%20or%20the%20top%20of%20the%20ticket%2C%26quot%3B%20Clyburn%20said%20on%20MSNBC%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Washington%2C%20where%20the%20optics%20are%20never%20far%20out%20of%20sight%2C%20it%20would%20be%20impossible%20to%20ignore%20passing%20over%20the%20first%20female%20vice%20president%20for%20a%20man%2C%20or%20the%20first%20Black%20vice%20president%20for%20a%20white%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20voters%20remain%20the%20core%20of%20the%20modern%20Democratic%20Party.%20No%20single%20group%20is%20a%20monolith%2C%20but%20none%20of%20the%20major%20Biden%20challengers%20come%20close%20to%20Harris'%20support%20in%20the%20Black%20community.%20According%20to%20a%20recent%20Economist-YouGov%20poll%2C%2066%25%20of%20Black%20voters%20view%20Harris%20favorably.%20In%20comparison%2C%20only%2047%25%20of%20Black%20voters%20view%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20favorably%3B%20slightly%20fewer%20view%20Michigan%20Gov.%20Gretchen%20Whitmer%20in%20the%20same%20light.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20survey%20found%20that%20voters%20still%20don't%20know%20enough%20about%20Whitmer%20to%20have%20an%20opinion%20about%20her%2C%20underlining%20another%20potential%20headache.%20Harris%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most-known%20politicians%20in%20the%20country.%20Any%20potential%20replacement%20will%20likely%20need%20to%20introduce%20themselves%20to%20the%20American%20people%20and%20on%20